            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Danger of Insurrection</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt>"We sleep as soundly and sweetly as though we were surrounded by an armed
                    body guard of chosen defenders, in the confident belief that our ebony friends
                    will not feel the slightest disposition to 'rise' until we chunk them up with a
                    long pole at the break of day."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Mocks Northern press coverage of Southern fears of insurrection. Author
                    claims that southerners sleep soundly, secure in the knowledge that slaves will
                    not rise up against them. Also expresses confidence that slavery was ordained by
                    God.</summary>
                <note>aubrowser/ssnov59.html#11.29c</note>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Charlestown Intelligence; (Correspondence of the Baltimore American);
                    Charlestown, Nov 23</head>
                <origin>Baltimore American</origin>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Yours, H. D. B. [followed by dispatch from Harper's Ferry]</trailer>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter from Charlestown, describing the goings on there, including Wise's
                    visit, as well as various rumors and scares.</summary>
                <note>aubrowser/ssnov59.html#11.29f</note>
            </div>
